  <section class="page-header">
    <h1>Issues</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Challenges I encountered while building animations and updating code.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- =========================
       MAIN CONTENT
       - Use semantic main + article + ol for clarity
  ========================== -->
  <main class="content" role="main">
    <article class="issue-list">
      <ol>
        <li>
          <h3>Issue 1 — Animation timing and smoothness</h3>
          <p>
            It was difficult to get the animations to run smoothly because I needed a modified
            code setup to match the environment I was using (I tested on <strong>One Compiler</strong>).
            Tweaking easing, durations, and transform properties helped improve smoothness.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <h3>Issue 2 — Outdated class materials</h3>
          <p>
            Many code examples from the class materials were outdated, so I had to update and
            remaster them — sometimes using AI to suggest modern alternatives for browser compatibility
            and new CSS/JS APIs.
          </p>
        </li>

        <li>
          <h3>Issue 3 — Hover/animation accuracy</h3>
          <p>
            Hover animations require precise values for transforms, timing, and easing; small values
            can cause noticeable jitter. I learned to test on multiple screen sizes and inspect the
            computed styles to refine the effect.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </article>
  </main>

